1
00:01:40,690 --> 00:01:44,280
[A Moment But Forever]

2
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:47,320
[Episode 15]

3
00:02:09,669 --> 00:02:10,750
Why are you here?

4
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:13,310
I was worried, so I came to find you.

5
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:17,350
What's wrong? You look unhappy.

6
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:18,960
Are the books not good?

7
00:02:23,390 --> 00:02:24,510
Are you hungry?

8
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,550
No.

9
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:27,070
You were busy all night yesterday,

10
00:02:27,270 --> 00:02:28,730
and you've been reading all day today.

11
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:30,150
How could you not be hungry?

12
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:32,510
Waiter, bring us some roast goose.

13
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:33,829
Alright, please wait a moment.

14
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:35,750
I thought they didn't have roast goose here.

15
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:37,350
I pre-ordered it yesterday.

16
00:02:38,270 --> 00:02:39,150
Thank you.

17
00:02:40,510 --> 00:02:41,430
You're welcome.

18
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,150
You're helping me out too.

19
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:46,550
Is the creation of the Linglong House

20
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:48,030
related to "The Book of Calming?"

21
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:49,329
What?

22
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,350
Not even remotely related.

23
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:53,030
No connection at all.

24
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:55,390
Then why did you buy these books?

25
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:56,590
None of your business.

26
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:08,460
How come the gambling game

27
00:03:08,990 --> 00:03:10,910
has turned into a music show?

28
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:12,470
A few days ago, Mei Shan

29
00:03:12,470 --> 00:03:13,940
got some attitude from your master,

30
00:03:14,310 --> 00:03:16,030
and he took it out on those gamblers.

31
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,150
I doubt anyone here

32
00:03:17,150 --> 00:03:17,700
will dare

33
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:18,829
to gamble again.

34
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:22,430
Your dishes are all here.

35
00:03:22,430 --> 00:03:23,190
Please enjoy.

36
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:38,840
Does time really not exist?

37
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:41,390
Still thinking about that?

38
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,190
Time indeed doesn't exist.

39
00:03:44,650 --> 00:03:46,090
It's just a concept.

40
00:03:46,510 --> 00:03:48,110
If time doesn't exist,

41
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:50,579
what's the meaning of living?

42
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:52,630
Although time isn't real,

43
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:54,710
the chess game we played,

44
00:03:54,950 --> 00:03:55,860
the wine we drank,

45
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,030
and the conversations we had—

46
00:03:57,050 --> 00:03:58,410
they all really happened.

47
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:01,310
So?

48
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,390
So,

49
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,030
what matters most in life

50
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,200
is the moments and experiences.

51
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:13,390
♫Lost in the mortal world♫

52
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:22,390
♫Love and hate come and go♫

53
00:04:26,790 --> 00:04:31,590
♫Drunk in foolish dreams♫

54
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:39,470
♫Cold or warm, only you will know♫

55
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:44,790
Those lyrics are quite interesting.

56
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:46,380
What's interesting about them?

57
00:04:48,550 --> 00:04:49,590
They're about life and death.

58
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:50,950
Did you not get that?

59
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:54,030
People of the Youhu Clan

60
00:04:54,030 --> 00:04:55,070
live a very long time.

61
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:56,870
How can you understand

62
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:58,110
the life and death of mortals?

63
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:00,110
Why does that sound

64
00:05:00,110 --> 00:05:01,110
so bitter?

65
00:05:01,550 --> 00:05:02,590
I'm not bitter.

66
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:06,350
The meaning of life doesn't lie in how long it lasts.

67
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,550
Immortals live for thousands of years,

68
00:05:08,990 --> 00:05:10,990
yet most of them spend their days cultivating in solitude.

69
00:05:11,030 --> 00:05:13,190
Meanwhile, mayflies live for only a day,

70
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:15,270
but they experience birth, aging, sickness, and death.

71
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:17,320
They know how to reproduce and sustain life.

72
00:05:17,470 --> 00:05:19,500
They too have their own

73
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,550
love, hate, and heartbreak.

74
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:22,950
So whether you live for 1,000 years

75
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:24,270
or just a single day,

76
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,470
what matters most is living the life you want

77
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,070
and feeling content and at ease.

78
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:30,990
Are you going to say time doesn't exist again?

79
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:32,630
You're too fixated on it.

80
00:05:32,990 --> 00:05:34,180
As long as you're happy,

81
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:36,030
why get hung up on the passing of time?

82
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:38,420
So,

83
00:05:38,790 --> 00:05:39,870
you're not afraid of death?

84
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:40,510
I am.

85
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,950
But fear won't change anything.

86
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:44,230
I have to accept it.

87
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:46,470
Greed has no limits,

88
00:05:46,490 --> 00:05:48,970
so don't obsess over life's length.

89
00:05:49,650 --> 00:05:51,100
Just like that song says,

90
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:52,710
even if this life

91
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:54,230
only holds a fleeting moment of joy,

92
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:55,750
remembering that feeling

93
00:05:55,990 --> 00:05:57,040
is enough.

94
00:05:58,030 --> 00:05:59,790
But the joy in that song

95
00:06:00,230 --> 00:06:01,790
seems to be about romantic love.

96
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:03,710
Romantic love,

97
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:04,910
obsessions,

98
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:06,070
or cravings…

99
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:07,350
It depends on

100
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:08,750
each person's understanding of joy.

101
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:11,310
What if someone gets that joy,

102
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:15,750
but after experiencing it,

103
00:06:16,070 --> 00:06:17,430
they no longer want to live?

104
00:06:18,390 --> 00:06:19,630
Wouldn't that be a pity?

105
00:06:19,870 --> 00:06:20,800
Then you'll have to ask

106
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,790
that person.

107
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:23,230
What feels like a pity to you

108
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:25,670
might not be a pity to them.

109
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:35,710
I'm heading back.

110
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,190
Sit back.

111
00:06:38,550 --> 00:06:39,470
Finish eating before you leave.

112
00:06:39,909 --> 00:06:41,600
Wasting food is not a good habit.

113
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:47,830
Why are you back?

114
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,580
I thought you had left

115
00:06:48,580 --> 00:06:49,750
for good.

116
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:51,390
What?

117
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:52,230
Why are you afraid of him?

118
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:53,430
Hey, old man, I'm talking to you.

119
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:54,230
Can't you hear me?

120
00:06:57,630 --> 00:06:58,430
Master.

121
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:01,030
You're back.

122
00:07:01,150 --> 00:07:02,950
I have something to ask you.

123
00:07:03,230 --> 00:07:04,040
Wait a moment.

124
00:07:04,670 --> 00:07:05,800
I need to talk to him.

125
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:10,910
High Priest,

126
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,790
my disciple seems to care a lot about you.

127
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:17,750
Oh, right.

128
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:19,070
Since we met,

129
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:20,710
I haven't given you any gifts.

130
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:21,740
Gifts?

131
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,430
Yuanzhong, Yuanzhong!

132
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:49,700
After taking my medicine,

133
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:50,830
he'll be fine in three to five days.

134
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,310
What a jerk!

135
00:07:53,590 --> 00:07:54,710
He caught Yuanzhong off guard.

136
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:55,630
So despicable.

137
00:07:55,740 --> 00:07:57,030
I curse him with a miserable death.

138
00:07:57,150 --> 00:07:58,310
Don't say that.

139
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,390
Fine.

140
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:06,710
Then what should I say?

141
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:54,710
Master, the tea is ready.

142
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:06,670
I don't understand.

143
00:09:07,190 --> 00:09:08,670
Why did you hurt Yuanzhong?

144
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:09,950
You're concerned for him?

145
00:09:11,540 --> 00:09:12,390
I'm not.

146
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:15,590
I hit him to avenge you.

147
00:09:16,310 --> 00:09:17,110
Avenge me?

148
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:21,630
60 years ago, during the Battle of Pinghu,

149
00:09:21,780 --> 00:09:22,750
a mysterious girl

150
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,150
appeared on the battlefield.

151
00:09:24,220 --> 00:09:25,450
She was attacked by Yuanzhong

152
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:27,710
and then sank into the sea

153
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,150
along with Pinghu Xianzhou.

154
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:30,430
That was you, right?

155
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:36,550
He hurt you back then,

156
00:09:36,620 --> 00:09:37,870
so he deserved that strike.

157
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:40,910
Besides, I wanted to test him

158
00:09:41,190 --> 00:09:42,670
to see if he's truly worthy…

159
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:45,430
of being with you.

160
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:47,320
After all,

161
00:09:47,470 --> 00:09:48,830
my most beloved disciple

162
00:09:48,950 --> 00:09:50,230
is no longer a mortal.

163
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:53,430
I'm not as good

164
00:09:53,430 --> 00:09:54,190
as you say, Master.

165
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:55,780
There are still many things

166
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:56,790
I don't understand,

167
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:58,390
and I can't be free of doubts.

168
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:01,470
Tell me.

169
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:03,670
What is it that you don't understand?

170
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:11,270
The four numbers you left behind,

171
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:12,900
no matter which version I checked,

172
00:10:13,110 --> 00:10:14,310
all point to a line

173
00:10:14,310 --> 00:10:15,110
from "The Book of Calming."

174
00:10:15,670 --> 00:10:16,480
What line?

175
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:19,910
"Shooting stars shine brilliantly. Even if they burn out, there's no regret."

176
00:10:21,110 --> 00:10:22,750
This line has another meaning:

177
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:26,470
"If one learns the Way in the morning, one can die without regret by evening."

178
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:33,350
I knew it.

179
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:36,280
I couldn't hide it from you.

180
00:10:42,310 --> 00:10:43,110
In this life,

181
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:44,790
I once prided myself on my craftsmanship.

182
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:47,310
I believed that no one in this world

183
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:48,470
could surpass me.

184
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:51,550
When I met you,

185
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:53,830
I knew right away you were gifted

186
00:10:53,830 --> 00:10:54,470
and thought you were

187
00:10:54,470 --> 00:10:56,030
the one chosen by heaven to inherit my skills.

188
00:10:56,330 --> 00:10:57,600
I wanted to take you as my disciple

189
00:10:58,190 --> 00:10:59,300
and teach you everything I knew.

190
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:03,900
But I was too narrow-minded.

191
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:06,430
You truly were the chosen one,

192
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:07,590
but what you were meant to inherit

193
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:09,740
was far greater than my humble craft.

194
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:10,950
Master…

195
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:15,830
Seeing you bring

196
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:16,950
my Linglong House design

197
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:18,470
to life

198
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:20,150
and ascend to godhood because of it...

199
00:11:22,670 --> 00:11:23,600
The whole thing

200
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,390
left me feeling down

201
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:26,390
for quite a while.

202
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:29,110
I started doubting my path

203
00:11:29,950 --> 00:11:30,790
and all the effort

204
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:33,010
I had poured into my craftsmanship.

205
00:11:36,910 --> 00:11:37,860
If craftsmanship

206
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:39,990
was truly my destined path,

207
00:11:41,070 --> 00:11:42,470
then why was it you

208
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:44,900
who became a god and not me?

209
00:11:52,710 --> 00:11:53,910
For the next few hundred years,

210
00:11:54,270 --> 00:11:55,590
I put aside my craftsmanship,

211
00:11:55,940 --> 00:11:57,390
traveled far and wide,

212
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:58,610
and turned to swordsmanship instead.

213
00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:01,950
By the grace of heaven, I was gifted

214
00:12:02,270 --> 00:12:03,510
and made some achievements.

215
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:07,280
But I always felt like

216
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:09,900
something was missing.

217
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:14,740
One day,

218
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:16,350
I stumbled upon a remote village

219
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,110
and saw an old carpenter

220
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:19,350
making tables and chairs.

221
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,660
He neither knew how to select materials

222
00:12:22,990 --> 00:12:24,270
nor had refined skills.

223
00:12:26,230 --> 00:12:27,470
But I stayed there,

224
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:30,830
quietly watching him for an entire day.

225
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:35,270
I watched him slowly turn planks of wood

226
00:12:36,430 --> 00:12:37,990
into tables and chairs.

227
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,910
In that moment, I finally understood

228
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:46,630
how much I loved craftsmanship.

229
00:12:47,790 --> 00:12:49,750
Cultivation and immortality

230
00:12:49,780 --> 00:12:51,260
meant nothing to me.

231
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:53,030
Only craftsmanship

232
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:55,510
could bring me joy.

233
00:12:57,590 --> 00:12:59,510
This kind of joy is small,

234
00:13:00,230 --> 00:13:02,110
and there's no need for others to understand it.

235
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,630
That simple joy

236
00:13:03,630 --> 00:13:04,950
you're talking about,

237
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:07,510
I've felt it too from time to time.

238
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:13,150
After that, I returned here,

239
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:14,990
turned my four unresolved questions

240
00:13:14,990 --> 00:13:16,310
into four seals,

241
00:13:16,710 --> 00:13:17,910
and sealed Yingong Mountain.

242
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:21,190
I understand now.

243
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:24,270
What you sealed wasn't just a mountain.

244
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:25,510
You also sealed

245
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:27,830
the passion for craftsmanship that you once had

246
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:29,540
when you first began teaching.

247
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:31,390
You sealed that chapter of your life

248
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:32,790
and your mindset back then.

249
00:13:35,390 --> 00:13:37,630
Exactly. That's it.

250
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:42,790
I knew it.

251
00:13:45,470 --> 00:13:46,910
Only you can understand me.

252
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:09,990
Now, of the four questions,

253
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:11,460
you've solved three.

254
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:13,630
Once you unravel the mystery of the Linglong House,

255
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:15,350
I'll have no regrets left.

256
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:19,310
Tanyin, on the last question,

257
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,230
I hope you can enlighten me.

258
00:14:22,070 --> 00:14:23,510
But Master, you haven't become a god.

259
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,910
You've lived for 1,000 years as a mortal

260
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:27,120
because of

261
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,310
that unwavering obsession.

262
00:14:29,590 --> 00:14:30,550
If I were to

263
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:31,910
resolve that obsession,

264
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:33,470
I fear you might

265
00:14:33,730 --> 00:14:35,960
perish in an instant.

266
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:41,860
"If one learns the Way in the morning, one can die without regret by evening."

267
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:43,390
If one carries

268
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:45,150
unanswered doubts in their heart,

269
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:47,070
life can lose its spark.

270
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:48,760
You're a craftsman.

271
00:14:49,270 --> 00:14:51,830
Please, fulfill my wish.

272
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:54,590
Master, don't…

273
00:14:57,310 --> 00:14:59,510
The more capable one is the master.

274
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:01,720
These four questions are your lessons to me.

275
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:02,560
So at this moment,

276
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:05,690
you are my master.

277
00:15:09,060 --> 00:15:10,030
I offer you my respect.

278
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:23,630
Alright.

279
00:15:26,110 --> 00:15:27,670
I know what you want now.

280
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:31,670
I'll take

281
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:35,230
this cup of tea.

282
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:57,430
Once my master, always my master.

283
00:15:58,860 --> 00:16:00,110
You're my master

284
00:16:01,470 --> 00:16:02,670
and always will be.

285
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,760
♫Racing forward, scars all over my body♫

286
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:18,060
♫Yet my gaze stays firm and unwavering♫

287
00:16:18,330 --> 00:16:23,280
♫Cutting through this cold, bitter world♫

